column1: 523|"Beauty - Cosmetics Executive Women membership"|"Skin Care"|"Wilcoxson," Megan""
column12: We provide CEW with a list of Cincinnati based Beauty employees", all levels and functions. The information we give is full name, physical work address, email address, prefix (Mr/Ms), and in some cases their titles or function. Employees opt into creating a CEW account," but they do not opt into providing their data.		More background from Jen Chamberlain:	CEW is a beauty industry membership organization", based on the US but with global relevancy. Our beauty industry budget funds the membership fees for P&G beauty employees. We allocate approximately 450 seats a year, which go to: all US-based commercial employees, all Band 6+ global beauty leadership," and the balance to selected technical organization employees and/or special interest groups. 		The names are pulled each year through a partnership with HR. Employees are notified of their membership", but we have not ever specifically told them that their email addresses are being passed along (which, yes they are), along with their work address and work function/title.  Each employee does need to activate their membership in order to receive certain CEW benefits," but I believe that CEW sends email blasts to everyone unless they opt out deliberately.  		Memberships are renewed in December of each year. ""

A third party customer service group handles calls for questions or for people seeking tickets for special cases/exception requests.""
